This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques for classifying key phrases in educational reports. The paper discusses the use of language models and TFIDF SVM classifiers, which are commonly used in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DL (Deep Learning). The paper also discusses information retrieval techniques, which are commonly used in sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of cybersecurity techniques, which are commonly used in sub-category cs.CY (Cybersecurity).
